        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/trump-travel-ban-deficient-vetting-deportation-refusal.jpg" alt="Trump said some countries had ‚Äúdeficient‚Äù screening and vetting or had historically refused to take back their citizens" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
         Trump said some countries had ‚Äúdeficient‚Äù screening and vetting or had historically refused to take back their citizens. Credits: AP Photo/Alex Brandon</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Trump has announced a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-spotlights-1-travel-ban" target="_blank">travel ban</a> affecting 19 countries, effective Monday. The ban fully blocks entry for nationals from 12 countries, including Afghanistan, Iran, Somalia, Libya, and Yemen. Another seven countries, including Cuba, Venezuela, Laos, and Sierra Leone, face minimal restrictions on immigrants and some nonimmigrant visa categories.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Trump cites national security risks and a lack of information sharing as reasons. He believes this decree is vital to keep foreign nationals from entering the US without proper vetting. This follows a recent <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-spotlights-2-attack-in-colorado" target="_blank">attack in Colorado</a> by an undocumented immigrant. He also noted that the list of banned nations may expand if newer threats arise. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Exceptions to the ban include lawful permanent residents, certain visa holders, and athletes in international events, such as the FIFA Club World Cup and the 2028 Olympics. Critics compare this ban to Trump‚Äôs <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-spotlights-3-2017-travel-ban" target="_blank">2017 travel ban</a>. Judicial and political challenges are expected.</p>
        </mj-text>
