          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
         36 years since Tiananmen </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
          Summary: The Tiananmen Square massacre happened 36 years ago, and victims still demand justice. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The US secretary of state and the Taiwan president said the world will not forget the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-spotlights-h2-7-tiananmen-square-massacre" target="_blank">Tiananmen Square massacre</a> on the 36th anniversary of the crackdown. They praised the courage of those who died for democracy and stressed the need to remember the victims.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       Many assert that the Chinese government is attempting to erase the memory of the incident. In China, authorities censor discussions about the massacre. Activists overseas, like Uyghurs, Tibetans, and Hongkongers, also face repression. Hong Kong, once a hub for annual vigils, currently bans these events under strict national security laws. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The ‚ÄúTiananmen Mothers,‚Äù parents of victims, demand justice for their lost children. They challenge the government‚Äôs efforts to silence history. The US Secretary of State and Taiwan‚Äôs President <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-spotlights-h2-8-observed-and-honored" target="_blank">observed and honored</a> this day. </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        On June 4, 1989, pro-democracy protesters, mainly students, faced violent suppression from military forces. </p>
        
        </mj-text>
