        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá¶üá´ Afghanistan - Expulsion from neighboring countries.</strong> Over 200,000 Afghans have left Pakistan since April 2025, following the government's renewed deportation drive targeting over 800,000 Afghans with canceled residence permits. The UN‚Äôs International Organization for Migration warns that the mass returns strain Afghanistan‚Äôs reintegration systems and calls for the suspension of forced returns until safe conditions are in place (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-10-the-deportations" target="_blank">the deportations</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá©üá∞ Denmark - Drops frugal stance.</strong> Denmark's PM Mette Frederiksen emphasized the need for increased defense funding to address the threat posed by Russia. As Denmark gets ready for its EU Council presidency, Frederiksen emphasized the need to rearm Europe (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-11-major-shift" target="_blank">major shift</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáÆüá© Indonesia - Bomber‚Äôs coffee business.</strong> Convicted terrorist Umar Patek, involved in the 2002 Bali bombings, has launched a coffee brand called Ramu in Indonesia. While promoting peace and de-radicalization, he faced a survivor of the attacks at the launch. Though he apologized, victims remain skeptical. Authorities and analysts cautiously support his rehabilitation efforts (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-12-reintegration-into-society" target="_blank">reintegration into society</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá¨üáß UK - Persian journalists threatened.</strong> 
           BBC Persian journalists in London report intensified harassment by the Iranian regime. Staff describe it as ‚Äúpsychological warfare,‚Äù meant to pressure them into silence. The BBC calls this a ‚Äúdeeply troubling escalation‚Äù and plans to complain to the UN Human Rights Council (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-13-about-the-threats" target="_blank">about the threats</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá®üá± Chile - Stolen babies.</strong> 
            Chile is prosecuting individuals accused of stealing babies during Augusto Pinochet‚Äôs dictatorship. A judge alleges a network of officials, priests, and others abducted infants from poor mothers and sold them abroad. Five people face charges, and Chile seeks the extradition of a former judge (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-14-more-adoption-scams" target="_blank">more adoption scams</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá®üá∫ Cuba - Accuses the US.</strong> 
            Cuban official Johana Tablada accused the Trump administration of raising tensions with Havana. Speaking in Washington, she criticized recent U.S. sanctions and diplomatic moves, including meetings with Cuban dissidents. She claimed this could lead to a military clash. Meanwhile, the US repeated its demands for Cuba to release political prisoners and start meaningful dialogue (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jun-25-worldwide-15-cuba-us-exchanges" target="_blank">Cuba-US exchanges</a>). 
          </p>
         
